main event: Two bright objects were spotted in the sky that moved rapidly and then disappeared into the clouds.
interesting points: The objects were described as being similar to stars but much brighter.
The objects moved rapidly from one place to another before disappearing into the clouds.
The observer was a civilian female with no technical or scientific background.
The investigating officer hypothesized that the objects could have been light metallic constructions transported by the wind, or chaff dropped by aircraft reflecting in the sun.
Local radar controllers stated that chaff is often discernible on their radar scopes for extended periods when upper winds are light.
result: Possible explanation (chaff or light metallic constructions)
sighted object: Two bright objects in the sky
